Name: Terran Firebat
Description: The Firebat is an infantry support unit. Its main attack is a flamethrower that consists of two short parallel line splash of 8 concussive damage. This is further enhanced by a radial splash of 8 concussive damage near the end of the flame that damages units that were not hit by both line splash attacks.

Name: Terran Ghost
Description: The Ghost is a specialised infantry-type spellcaster unit. The Ghost has a long ranged attack that deals 10 concussive damage at a rapid rate, but its real power lies in its special abilities.

Name: Terran Goliath
Description: The Goliath is most useful for its powerful anti-air attack, although it can attack both air and ground targets. It has high range and deals substantial damage to the opponent's air units.

Name: Terran Marine
Description: The Marine is the base Terran combat unit. When upgraded with Stim Packs, it can sacrifice 10 hit points in order to double its rate of fire and increase move speed. Marines work very well with medics. They can be loaded into a Bunker, protecting them and further increasing their range by one.

Name: Terran Medic
Description: The Medic its primary function healing friendly biological units. Healing is automatic but directable and causes the Medic to use up exhaustible energy like a spellcaster (2HP per 1 energy).

Name: Terran SCV
Description: The SCV (Space Construction Vehicle) is the Terran worker unit. It harvests resources, constructs buildings and can repair all Terran mechanical units and buildings.

Name: Terran Siege Tank Siege Mode
Description: The Siege Tank, or simply Tank, is a Terran mechanical unit. While in Siege Mode, the Siege Tank is incapable of movement and gains a range of 12, but also has a minimum range of 2. The Siege Tank is able to freely transform between the two modes with a short transformation sequence.

Name: Terran Siege Tank Tank Mode
Description: The Siege Tank, or simply Tank, is a Terran mechanical unit. A Siege Tank in Tank Mode deals 30 explosive damage, and one that is in Siege Mode deals 70 explosive damage plus splash. These can further be upgraded at the Armory. The Siege Tank is able to freely transform between the two modes with a short transformation sequence.

Name: Terran Vulture
Description: The Vulture is an extremely mobile and dangerous Terran unit produced from the Factory. Vultures are the epitome of cost-efficiency; properly microed, they can take down an unlimited number of some units and Spider Mines give them further unique potential cost-efficiency.

Name: Terran Vulture Spider Mine
Description: Spider Mines are placed on the ground by Vultures. Once deployed, the mine burrows into the ground rendering it invisible. When a unit comes into range, the mine unburrows and, after a brief delay, launches itself at the target far faster than most units can avoid. A player cannot manually order mines to move.

Name: Terran Battlecruiser
Description: The Battlecruiser (Commonly abbreviated as BC) is one of the strongest air units in the game. However, its cost, build time, and high supply requirement  makes sure that it is also one of the lesser used units in competitive StarCraft. When Battlecruisers do get used, the Yamato Gun upgrade is very popular due to its extremely high damage.

Name: Terran Dropship
Description: The Dropship is the Terran air transport unit.Compared to the other transport units, the Zerg Overlord and the Protoss Shuttle, the Dropship has the fastest movement speed. While the Overlord and Shuttle speeds can be upgraded, the Dropship has no further speed upgrade available.

Name: Terran Science Vessel
Description: The Science Vessel is an airborne detector caster unit. In the Terran army, it generally serves a support role. It's casting abilities are especially important in late game scenarios.

Name: Terran Valkyrie
Description: The Valkyrie is a Terran air-to-air unit. Valkyries employ an air-to-air attack that issues a volley of eight small missiles at its target. These missiles impact not only on their target, but also damage any enemy units within a 3 x 3 matrix area. Each missile does a small amount of splash damage in this target area.

Name: Terran Wraith
Description: The Wraith is the initial Terran air unit which can be built from the Starport without any addons. It deals 8 normal damage against ground units, and 20 explosive damage against air units. It can be upgraded with Cloak, which renders it invisible, and it can be upgraded with an energy upgrade to give it 50 extra energy.

Name: Terran Academy
Description: The Academy, like the Armory, does not produce Terran units, but instead provides the technology for its complementary building, the Barracks, to do so.

Name: Terran Armory
Description: The Armory is a building constructed by Terran to enable production of advanced units such as Valkyries and Goliaths. In addition there are four available upgrades from the Armory.

Name: Terran Barracks
Description: The Barracks (or Rax for short) is the infantry production building for Terran.

Name: Terran Bunker
Description: The Bunker is an important Terran defensive structure. Unlike defensive buildings like the Missile Turret, Zerg Sunken Colony or Protoss Photon Cannon, the Bunker does not directly attack (i.e. defend against) opponents on its own. To be effective, the Bunker must be filled with one to four infantry units.

Name: Terran Command Center
Description: The Command Center (Commonly abbreviated as CC) is the most important Terran building. Terran players start the game with one Command Center. It produces SCVs, the worker unit, and is at the root of the Terran Tech tree.

Name: Terran Engineering Bay
Description: The Engineering Bay (commonly abbreviated as E-Bay) is a building constructed by Terran for the purpose of improving infantry weapons and armor. It also allows the player to construct Missile Turrets, so building an Engineering Bay is common even if infantry upgrades are not researched.

Name: Terran Factory
Description: The Factory is a Terran building that can be used to produce the Vulture, Siege Tank, and Goliath. No research upgrades can be directly performed on the Factory, but a Machine Shop add-on can be constructed onto the Factory that allows various upgrades relating to Factory-produced units.

Name: Terran Missile Turret
Description: The Missile Turret (or Turret for short) is a Terran defensive building, which once constructed will attack flying units and buildings. It cannot be lifted off. It is also one of the modes of detection for Terran as it reveals cloaked units (including ground units) within its range of attack.

Name: Terran Refinery
Description: The Refinery is the gas extraction building for Terran. When constructed on top of a Vespene Gas Geyser it allows the Terran player to collect Vespene Gas by sending SCVs into it.

Name: Terran Science Facility
Description: The Science Facility is an advanced tech/late game building built by Terran following construction of the Starport. Although the Science Facility does not directly build any units, they enable the production of the Science Vessel at Starports.

Name: Terran Starport
Description: The Starport is an advanced building constructed by Terran. Its primarily serves to construct air units.

Name: Terran Supply Depot
Description: The Supply Depot is a building constructed by Terran for the purpose of providing supply. Each Supply Depot raises the Terran's population limit by eight.

Name: Terran Comsat Station
Description: The Comsat Station add-on, often called a "Scanner," allows Terran to gain vision and Detection over a finite area on the map for a short amount of time (from about seven to ten seconds).

Name: Terran Control Tower
Description: The Control Tower is a Terran add-on for the Starport. This add-on allows the production of Dropships amongst other units and upgrades.

Name: Terran Covert Ops
Description: The Covert Ops is an add-on for the Terran Science Facility. The Covert Ops unlocks the ability to produce Ghosts from the Barracks and Nukes.

Name: Terran Machine Shop
Description: The Machine Shop is a Terran add-on for the Factory. It allows the production of Siege Tanks from the Factory and Tier Two Tech upgrades.

Name: Terran Nuclear Silo
Description: The Nuclear Silo is an add-on to the Command Center that allows the Terran player to build and store one Nuclear Missile. Each armed Nuclear Missile costs eight supply, 200 minerals and 200 gas. Once it is armed, a Ghost can launch the Nuke.

Name: Terran Physics Lab
Description: The Physics Lab is an add-on for the Terran Science Facility. The other available add-on for the Science Facility is the Covert Ops and only one add-on can be attached and utilized at a time.

Name: Protoss Archon
Description: The Archon is a powerful Protoss unit formed when two High Templar decide to become an Archon by merging.

Name: Protoss Dark Archon
Description: The Dark Archon is a Protoss spell-caster that does not have the ability to attack directly. Rather, it is a supporting Protoss unit that is capable of three powerful spells. It is formed by merging two Dark Templars, which are produced by the Gateway.

Name: Protoss Dark Templar
Description: The Dark Templar, commonly abbreviated as DT, is a permanently cloaked Protoss ground unit. It is built from the Gateway if there is an existing Templar Archives.

Name: Protoss Dragoon
Description: The Dragoon is a ranged ground unit that can be warped in at the Protoss Gateway if a Cybernetics Core has been warped in. They are one of the most versatile units in the game.

Name: Protoss High Templar
Description: The High Templar is a Protoss spell-caster unit. It is considered one of the most powerful non-attack units in the game due to its Psionic Storm.

Name: Protoss Probe
Description: The Probe is the Protoss worker. It harvests Resources, has a low-powered ranged attack (with a range of one), and can build any Protoss building.

Name: Protoss Reaver
Description: The Reaver is a powerful Protoss siege unit produced from the Robotics Facility. Construction of Reavers also requires the Robotics Support Bay. The Robotics Support Bay also provides various upgrades to increase the potency of the Reaver.

Name: Protoss Scarab
Description: Scarabs are projectiles produced by Reavers that are required for the Reaver to attack. Scarabs are individually produced and stored in the Reaver until the Reaver is ordered to attack.

Name: Protoss Zealot
Description: The Zealot is the Protoss first tier melee unit. Zealots only deal damage to ground units, so are vulnerable to air attack units.

Name: Protoss Arbiter
Description: The Arbiter is one of the highest technology units in the Protoss arsenal. It's a support unit with a passive ability which cloaks any units underneath it.

Name: Protoss Carrier
Description: Carriers are a late-game Protoss air unit that are the largest and most costly unit available for Protoss. Carriers are produced from the Stargate and requires a pre-existing Fleet Beacon.

Name: Protoss Corsair
Description: First introduced in the expansion set, Corsairs are fast, highly mobile units with considerable harassing and scouting potential. They have a small 50% splash attack that is very useful against clumps of enemy air units.

Name: Protoss Interceptor
Description: Interceptors are small flying attacking units built and transported by Carriers. The player cannot control them; they are launched automatically when the Carrier is given an attack command and quickly fly in roughly circular paths around the target attacking it.

Name: Protoss Observer
Description: The Observer is a permanently cloaked Protoss air unit that cannot attack. Its primary purpose is for scouting and Detection.

Name: Protoss Scout
Description: The Scout is a power Protoss air unit that is produced from the Stargate.

Name: Protoss Shuttle
Description: The Shuttle is the Protoss's transport unit. It is slow at first, but its speed can be upgraded at the Robotics Support Bay.

Name: Protoss Arbiter Tribunal
Description: The Arbiter Tribunal is a building warped-in by Protoss for the main purpose of allowing the production of Arbiters from the Stargate.

Name: Protoss Assimilator
Description: The Arbiter Tribunal is a building warped-in by Protoss for the main purpose of allowing the production of Arbiters from the Stargate.

Name: Protoss Citadel of Adun
Description: The Citadel of Adun, or Citadel for short, is a building warped-in by Protoss as a prerequisite for the Templar Archives. Additionally, the Citadel researches the Zealot Leg Enhancements upgrade.

Name: Protoss Cybernetics Core
Description: The Cybernetics Core is an important Protoss tech building. It unlocks the production of the Protoss ranged ground unit, the Dragoon, and allows the research of the Dragoon range upgrade. It unlocks advanced buildings.

Name: Protoss Fleet Beacon
Description: The Fleet Beacon is a Protoss technology building at the very end of its tech tree. The Fleet Beacon opens up several aerial upgrades as well as allowing the Protoss player to construct Carriers. . It also unlocks second and third levels or air weapons and air armor upgrades at the Cybernetics Core.

Name: Protoss Forge
Description: The Forge allows the Protoss player to build Photon Cannons, a highly versatile and cheap defensive structure. It also allows the Protoss player to access three upgrades: ground attack, ground armor and shields.

Name: Protoss Gateway
Description: The Gateway is a Protoss building that is used for building infantry units. Protoss players make heavy use of every unit produced at the Gateway, making it the most important production building in every Protoss match-up.

Name: Protoss Nexus
Description: The Nexus is the most important Protoss building. It produces Probes, the worker unit, and is at the root of the Protoss tech tree. It is also the Protoss resource gathering center; without it the player cannot gather resources.

Name: Protoss Observatory
Description: The Observatory is an advanced Protoss building. It allows the Robotics Facility to produce Observers, which are very useful for scouting, as they are permanently cloaked and are also detectors The Observatory allows the research of a sight range and movement speed upgrade for Observers.

Name: Protoss Photon Cannon
Description: The Photon Cannon, often simply called a Cannon, is a versatile Protoss defensive building capable of attacking both air and ground targets with a ranged attack. They are also detectors for the Protoss, thus often used to counter cloaked opponent units.

Name: Protoss Pylon
Description: The Pylon is a vital Protoss building. Pylons are warped in for the dual purpose of providing Psi, which raises the population limit, and for providing the Psionic Matrix, which extends in a circle outward from the Pylon.

Name: Protoss Robotics Facility
Description: The Robotics Facility (or Robo for short) allows the production of Shuttles, a flying transport unit which allows the player to bypass cliffs and access islands. It also allows the construction of more advanced robotics buildings: the Robotics Support Bay and the Observatory.

Name: Protoss Robotics Support Bay
Description: The Robotics Support Bay is an advanced Protoss building. It allows the Robotics Facility to produce Reavers and unlocks a speed upgrade for Shuttles. It also offers upgrades that make Reavers more effective by increasing its Scarab capacity and the damage dealt by Scarabs.

Name: Protoss Shield Battery
Description: The Shield Battery is an uncommonly used Protoss defensive building which can replenish the Plasma Shields of an injured Protoss unit.

Name: Protoss Stargate
Description: The Stargate is a building warped in by Protoss for the main purpose of producing most of the air units in the Protoss arsenal.

Name: Protoss Templar Archives
Description: The Templar Archives is an advanced Protoss tech building. The structure allows the Protoss to produce High Templars and Dark Templars from the Gateway. In addition, the Templar Archives allow the unlocking of level 2 and 3 ground weapon and armor at the Forge.

Name: Zerg Broodling
Description: The Broodling is a small Zerg unit spawned when a Queen casts Spawn Broodling on a target. Two Broodlings spawn per spell cast. Upon their creation, they have a fixed amount of "energy" that represents their life span.

Name: Zerg Defiler
Description: The Defiler is a Zerg Hive tech unit. It is one of the Zerg's most powerful spell casters. A support unit, it is most well known for its Dark Swarm and Plague abilities.

Name: Zerg Drone
Description: The Drone is the Zerg Worker. It can gather Minerals and Vespene Gas, it has a low-damage ranged attack, and it can morph into a Zerg building anywhere on the Creep generated from Creep Colonies and Hatcheries, even when the creep is created by neutral or enemy buildings.

Name: Zerg Egg
Description: The Egg is the unit Larvae and Hydralisks turn into during the morphing process to another Zerg unit (Lurkers for Hydralisks). An Egg has a very high armor value, making it hard to kill.

Name: Zerg Hydralisk
Description: The Hydralisk is a versatile Zerg ranged unit that can attack both air and ground targets using needle spines. Hydralisks can be morphed from Larvae after building a Hydralisk Den. Hydralisks deal explosive damage, which makes them good against buildings and large units.

Name: Zerg Infested Terran
Description: The Infested Terran is a rarely-used Zerg suicide unit produced from the Infested Command Center, which is created by Queens from damaged Command Centers.

Name: Zerg Larva
Description: The Larva (Plural: Larvae) is a Zerg unit that automatically spawns directly below every Hatchery, Lair, and Hive, with a maximum of 3 Larvae at any one of these buildings.

Name: Zerg Lurker
Description: The Lurker is a unique unit added in the Brood Wars expansion in that it attacks while burrowed with linear splash spikes. The Lurker is morphed from the Hydralisk after the appropriate Lair-tech upgrade is researched from the Hydralisk Den.

Name: Zerg Ultralisk
Description: The Ultralisk is a late-game Hive-tech unit that is only available once the Zerg player has an Ultralisk Cavern. It is very expensive with 200 Vespene Gas but has a great deal of health and Zergling-like after upgrades.

Name: Zerg Zergling
Description: The Zergling is the earliest attack unit the Zerg player has access to. Zerglings can be morphed after construction of the Spawning Pool. They are melee units with low health individually but incredible damage for the cost.

Name: Zerg Cocoon
Description: The Cocoon is the transitional Zerg unit Mutalisks turn into during the morphing process to Guardians or Devourers.

Name: Zerg Devourer
Description: The Devourer is a rarely used Hive-tech exclusively air-to-air unit that requires a Greater Spire to morph from a Mutalisk, through a Cocoon.

Name: Zerg Guardian
Description: The Guardian is a Zerg Hive-tech flying siege unit. Guardians are morphed from Mutalisks. The Guardian is very slow moving, but its power lies in its long attack range.

Name: Zerg Mutalisk
Description: The Mutalisk is a fast moving air unit. Its attack deals the same damage against ground units making it a potent harasser and its health and mobility makes it a match for other single-target air-to-air units and low masses of most ground-to-air units with Zerg's typical economy.

Name: Zerg Overlord
Description: The Overlord is a multi-purpose Zerg supply providing unit. It has a long sight range and is a detector. Zerg players start with one Overlord at the start of a game.

Name: Zerg Queen
Description: The Queen is a quick-flying Zerg air unit with the ability to cast multiple spells.

Name: Zerg Scourge
Description: Scourge are suicidal Zerg anti-air units that require a Spire and thus Lair-tech to build. They serve as the Zerg primary airborne anti-air with Mutalisk.

Name: Zerg Creep Colony
Description: The Creep Colony are Zerg structures that extend the Creep, on which the Zerg can place its buildings. It can also morph into two types of defensive static buildings.

Name: Zerg Defiler Mound
Description: The Defiler Mound is an essential high-tech building for the Zerg. The Defiler Mound does not build any units directly, but rather enables Defiler production at the Hive. Various upgrades affecting the Defiler can be researched at the Defiler Mound

Name: Zerg Evolution Chamber
Description: The Evolution Chamber is a Zerg building that allows the Zerg player to morph Creep Colonies into Spore Colonies, which both act as detectors and as anti-air defensive buildings.

Name: Zerg Extractor
Description: he Extractor is a required building for Zerg to harvest Vespene Gas Extractors can only be built on Vespene Gas Geysers.

Name: Zerg Greater Spire
Description: The Greater Spire is morphed from the Zerg Spire and requires a Hive to be morphed. It allows the Zerg player's Mutalisks to morph into Guardians and Devourers. The Greater Spire does not build any units directly.

Name: Zerg Hatchery
Description: The Hatchery is the Zerg's most important building. The Hatchery allows the harvesting of resources and automatically creates Larvae over time. Each Hatchery will only produce up to three Larvae until Larvae are morphed into other Zerg Units

Name: Zerg Hive
Description: The Hive is a key building for Zerg technology. The Hive originates from morphing of the Lair and is the last stage of the Hatchery tech tree. It enables the construction of buildings such as the Greater Spire, Ultralisk Cavern, Nydus Canal and Defiler Mound.

Name: Zerg Hydralisk Den
Description: The Hydralisk Den is an early to mid game Zerg tech building that allows the Zerg player to create Hydralisks. The Hydralisk Den does not produce units directly, but rather enable Hydralisk morphing at the Hatchery. The Hydralisk Den allows upgrades to the speed and range of Hydralisks.

Name: Zerg Infested Command Center
Description: An Infested Command Center is a rarely seen building that is produced when a Queen uses Infest Command Center on a damaged Command Center. The Command Center must have less than 750/1500 HP to be infested.

Name: Zerg Lair
Description: The Lair is a key building for Zerg technology. The Lair is the second stage of the Hatchery tech tree. Originating from morphing of the Hatchery, the Lair can then be morphed into the Hive after the Queen's Nest is built.

Name: Zerg Nydus Canal
Description: The Nydus Canal allows the Zerg player to instantly transport ground units between the two linked Nydus Canals. After the Nydus Canal is built, a second Nydus Canal (called a Nydus Canal Exit) can then be built on Creep anywhere on the map that is within vision.

Name: Zerg Queens Nest
Description: The Queen's Nest allows the Zerg player to upgrade the Lair into a Hive. The Queen's Nest does not build any units directly, but enables the Queen to be morphed at the Lair or Hive. The structure also allows the research of the Queen's available upgrades.

Name: Zerg Spawning Pool
Description: The Spawning Pool is the first building Zerg that can be morphed in a new Starcraft match, after the Hatchery. Construction of the Spawning Pool unlocks the ability of the Hatchery to morph Zerglings.

Name: Zerg Spire
Description: The Spire is a mid-game Zerg tech building that allows the player to create Mutalisks and Scourge, both of which are built at the Hatchery. The Spire does not build any units directly.

Name: Zerg Spore Colony
Description: The Spore Colony is a Zerg base anti-air defense structure. It deals 15 points of damage with a high rate of fire and provides the Zerg with static detection of cloaked units.

Name: Zerg Sunken Colony
Description: The Sunken Colony is a Zerg base defense structure that deals 40 explosive damage. The Sunken Colony requires Spawning Pool technology before it can be morphed from Creep Colony.

Name: Zerg Ultralisk Cavern
Description: The Ultralisk Cavern is a late-game Tech building created by Zerg for the purpose of allowing the production of Ultralisks. Ultralisks are produced at the Hive, as the Ultralisk Cavern does not build any units.
